<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">From British Legation.</hi></head>
                        <note rend="inline"><hi rend="italic">Memorandum.—Case of the Mont
                                Blanc.</hi></note>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-08-10"><hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 10, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>In a note dated the 16th of July Lord Lyons observed that on being
                            informed by Mr. Seward that directions to proceed to the assessment of
                            damages in this case would be given to Rear-Admiral Bailey, he would, on
                            his part, take care that proper directions should be sent to Mr.
                            Vice-Consul Butterfield.</p>
                        <p>Lord Lyons is waiting for this information before taking any further
                            steps.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>